# MiroFish — Codebase Explanation (Block by Block)

## What is MiroFish?

**MiroFish** is a *Swarm Intelligence Prediction Engine*.  
You feed it seed documents (news reports, policy drafts, novel chapters…), describe a prediction goal in plain language, and it automatically:

1. Builds a **knowledge graph** of all entities in the documents (using **Zep Cloud**).
2. Turns each entity into an **AI Agent** with a unique personality and memory.
3. Runs a dual-platform social-media **simulation** (Twitter + Reddit) powered by the **OASIS** framework.
4. Has a **Report Agent** analyse the simulation and produce a detailed prediction report.
5. Lets you **chat** with any simulated agent or with the Report Agent after the simulation.

---

## High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Browser["Vue 3 Frontend\n(port 3000)"]
    Flask["Flask Backend\n(port 5001)"]
    Zep["Zep Cloud\n(Knowledge Graph)"]
    LLM["LLM API\n(OpenAI-compatible)"]
    OASIS["OASIS Simulation\n(Twitter + Reddit)"]

    Browser -->|REST/JSON| Flask
    Flask -->|Zep SDK| Zep
    Flask -->|OpenAI SDK| LLM
    Flask -->|subprocess / IPC| OASIS
```

---

## Repository Layout

```
MiroFish/
├── .env / .env.example        # All secrets & runtime config
├── package.json               # Root npm scripts (dev, setup, build)
├── docker-compose.yml         # One-command Docker deploy
├── Dockerfile                 # Single-container image
├── backend/                   # Python / Flask
│   ├── run.py                 # Entrypoint
│   └── app/
│       ├── __init__.py        # Flask app factory
│       ├── config.py          # All Config vars (read from .env)
│       ├── api/               # HTTP route blueprints
│       ├── models/            # Data model classes (Project, Task)
│       ├── services/          # Business logic
│       └── utils/             # Shared helpers
└── frontend/                  # Vue 3 + Vite
    └── src/
        ├── main.js            # App entry point
        ├── App.vue            # Root component / layout shell
        ├── router/index.js    # Client-side routes
        ├── api/               # Axios wrappers
        ├── store/             # Pinia global state
        ├── views/             # Page-level Vue components
        └── components/        # Reusable UI components
```

