## Block 20 — [api/simulation.py](file:///f:/Courses/AIExperiments/MiroFish/backend/app/api/simulation.py) (Simulation API Routes)

**File:** [backend/app/api/simulation.py](file:///f:/Courses/AIExperiments/MiroFish/backend/app/api/simulation.py)

Registered at `/api/simulation`. Key endpoints:

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/entities/<graph_id>` | GET | Retrieve & filter graph entities |
| `/create` | POST | Create a simulation record |
| `/prepare` | POST | Kick off async agent/config generation |
| `/prepare/status` | POST | Poll preparation progress |
| `/<sim_id>` | GET | Get simulation status |
| `/start` | POST | Start the OASIS child processes |
| `/stop` | POST | Stop the running simulation |
| `/interview` | POST | Ask a specific simulated agent a question |
| `/posts/<sim_id>` | GET | Stream simulated social-media posts |

Smart idempotency: `/prepare` checks if all necessary files already exist (via [_check_simulation_prepared()](file:///f:/Courses/AIExperiments/MiroFish/backend/app/api/simulation.py#239-356)) and returns immediately if the simulation is already ready — avoid re-generating.

**Interview feature:** Before sending the question to the agent, a prefix is prepended (`"结合你的人设...不调用工具直接用文本回复:"`) to suppress tool-calling and get a plain-text answer.

---

## Block 21 — [api/report.py](file:///f:/Courses/AIExperiments/MiroFish/backend/app/api/report.py) (Report API Routes)

**File:** [backend/app/api/report.py](file:///f:/Courses/AIExperiments/MiroFish/backend/app/api/report.py)

Registered at `/api/report`. Key endpoints:

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/generate` | POST | Start async report generation |
| `/generate/status` | POST | Poll generation progress |
| `/<report_id>` | GET | Fetch full report metadata + Markdown |
| `/<report_id>/sections` | GET | Fetch only completed sections (streaming UX) |
| `/<report_id>/section/<n>` | GET | Fetch one specific section |
| `/<report_id>/progress` | GET | Real-time generation progress |
| `/<report_id>/agent-log` | GET | Incremental agent log (from_line param) |
| `/by-simulation/<sim_id>` | GET | Look up report by simulation ID |
| `/check/<sim_id>` | GET | Is interview feature unlocked? |
| `/chat` | POST | Multi-turn Q&A with Report Agent |
| `/<report_id>/download` | GET | Download full Markdown file |

The `from_line` parameter on `/agent-log` enables **incremental polling** — the frontend requests only new log lines since the last fetch, avoiding resending the full log.

