## Block 25 — Backend Scripts (`backend/scripts/`)

These are standalone Python scripts launched by `SimulationRunner` as child processes:

- `run_twitter_simulation.py` — runs OASIS Twitter simulation, reads `simulation_config.json`, writes post data back via IPC.
- `run_reddit_simulation.py` — same for Reddit.
- `run_parallel_simulation.py` — starts both Twitter and Reddit in parallel threads.

Scripts stay in `backend/scripts/` and are **not** copied to the simulation data directory, so the same scripts are reused across all simulations.

---

## Block 26 — `docker-compose.yml` & `Dockerfile`

**`docker-compose.yml`** — single service, single container image `ghcr.io/666ghj/mirofish:latest`.  
- Exposes ports `3000` (frontend served by Nginx or Node) and `5001` (Flask).
- Mounts `./backend/uploads` into the container so simulation data, reports, and uploaded files persist across container restarts.
- Reads `./env` automatically.

The Dockerfile builds both the frontend (Vite build) and installs the Python dependencies, then packages everything into one container.

---

## Full Data Flow Summary

```
User uploads documents + describes goal
    ↓  POST /api/graph/ontology/generate
    ↓  LLM analyses documents → ontology (entity + edge types)
    ↓  project_id returned to frontend

User confirms ontology
    ↓  POST /api/graph/build
    ↓  Background thread:
           Zep graph created
           Document chunks added as Episodes
           Wait for Zep to process (entity extraction)
    ↓  task_id polled until graph_completed

User starts simulation
    ↓  POST /api/simulation/create
    ↓  POST /api/simulation/prepare (async)
           Read Zep entities → filter to ontology types
           LLM generates each entity's social-media persona (parallel)
           LLM picks simulation parameters (rounds, timing, etc.)
    ↓  status = READY

User runs simulation
    ↓  POST /api/simulation/start
    ↓  OASIS child processes:
           Twitter agents interact: post, like, repost, follow
           Reddit agents interact: post, comment, upvote, search
    ↓  Real-time post feed streamed to frontend

User generates report
    ↓  POST /api/report/generate
    ↓  ReportAgent:
           Plans outline (LLM)
           For each section: calls Zep search + post analysis tools,
                             writes section (LLM), saves section file
    ↓  Full Markdown report assembled

User chats
    ↓  POST /api/report/chat           → Q&A with Report Agent
    ↓  POST /api/simulation/interview  → Q&A with any simulated character
```
